raw_entry:
JOHN KELLEY, 125 acs. (N. L.),
Is. cf Wight Co: on S. side of Nottoway Riv; on N. side the Hornett Sw;
16 June 1714, p. 180. 15 Shill.

WILLIAM ATWOOD, 90 acs. (N.
L.), Pr. Anne Co., in Lynhaven Par;
beg. by a Gr. Cypress Sw., cor. of John
Atwood; on E. side of the Wear Br;
16 Dec, 1714, p. 208. Imp. of 2 pers:
James Smith & Susanna his wife.

WALTER JONES, 159 acs, (Escheat
L.), Pr. Anne Co., in Lynhaven Par;
in Little Creek; adj. James Wishard;
& Henry Collings’ land; 16 Dec. 1714,
p. 209. Escheated from Hester Bridge,
dec’d., by inquisition under William
Randolph, Gent., Esch’r., for 300 acs;
by survey found to contain 159 acs;
being part of a deed of sale from Col.
Adam Thorowgood to Hester Holmes,
for 300 acs., 19 Feb. 1658, who intermarried with George Bateman, & after
his decease intermarry’d with Thomas
Bridge. Now granted, &c; 2 Lbs, Tobacco, &c.

WILLIAM LEA. 100 acs. (Escheat
L.). K. & Q. Co., in St. Stephen's Par;
on W. side of Mr. John Madison's
Mill Sw. on N. side of Mattapony Riv;
adj. John Taylor; Mrs. Anne Wiltshire;
& Thomas Camp; 16 Dec, 1714, p. 214.
Escheated fromm Thomas Ware. decd.
by inquisition under Matthew Page.
Esqr.. Esch’r., 13 Oct. 1703: &c. 2
Lbs. Tobacco.

NATHANIEL SMITH, 112 acs. (N.
L.), New Kent Co., in St. Peter’s Par;
adj. Wm. Waddell: Thos, Jackson;
yemes Taylor; Wm, Vaughn; & Crump’s
Vine: 23 Dec. 1714, p. 227, 15 Shill.

ISAAC LAFEIT, 133 acs. (N. L.),
Henrico Co; on ‘S$, side of James Riv;
cut of the upper part of the last 5,000
acs. surveyed for the French Refugees;
beg. at John Calvet & his own corner;
23 ‘Dec. 1714, p. 229. Imp. of 3 pers:
Isaac Lafaite, Eliza. Lafaite, & Ester
Lafaite.

WILLIAM CAIN, 82 acs. (N. L.),
Is, of Wight Co; S. side of Nottoway
Riv., & on E. side of Tarraroe Cr;
down run of the Sweat House Swamp;
23 Mar. 1715, p. 267. 10 Shill.

SAME. 350 acs. (N, L.), Surry Co;
on §. side the main Black Water Sw;
on S, side the Little Sw., cor. of his
old land; 23 Mar. 1715, p. 271. 35
Shill.

CHARLES WINFREE, 76 acs. (N.
L.), New Kent Co., in St. Peter’s Par;
on brs. of Pouncy Cr; beg. at mouth of
Nutton’s Br. of said Cr; to Mill Sw;
20 Oct, 1716, p. 289. 10 Shill.

MOSES LIVERAN, 117 acs. (N. L.),
Henrico Co; on S, side of James River;
adj, John Forecuran; & John Martin;
31 Oct. 1716, p. 293. Part of the ist
5,000 acs. surveyed for the French
Refugees.

JOHN JONES, 53 acs. (N. L.),
Henrico Co; on S. side of James: River;
adj. James Bilbaud; on Dillwait’s line;
31 Oct. 1716, p. 296. Part of the first
5,000 acs. surveyed for the French Refugees,

JOHN FARCEE, 40 acs. (N. L.),
Henrico Co; on S. side of James River;
adj. Stephen Chastaine; on Abra. ;
to back line of the French Lands, &c;
31 Oct. 1716, p. 296. Part of the ist
5,000 acs. surveyed for the French
Refugees.

JACOB AMONET, 88 acs. (N. L.),
Henrico Co; on S. side of James River;
adj. Peter Sabotte; & John Chastaine;
31 Oct. 1716, p. 297. Part of the ist
5,000 acs. surveyed for the French
Refugees.

HENRY RAINES, WILLIAM HOWARD, & JOHN SUTTON, 464 acs. (N.
L.), K. & Q. Co., in St. Stephen’s Par;
beg. in old line of Prossor & Pannell’s;
to S. side of the N. fork of Otterdam
Swamp; 31 Oct. 1716, p. 299. 50 Shill.

WILLIAM CRAFFORD, 1129 acs.
(O. & N. L.), Norf. Co; on W. side
of the mouth cf the Southern Br. of
Eliz, Riv; beg. at mouth of Creb Cr;
adj. Wm. Bustin; on N. side of Parrodice Cr; to mouth of the Reedy Er;
on Edward Hues’ line or Henry Low’s;
to E. side of Church Cr; to Joshua
Curle’s; down S, side cf the Island Cr;
31 Oct. 1716, p. 299. Found within
patent co Capt. Wm. Carver, 15 Sept.
1664, for 890 acs. 25 Shill.

ROBERT BURTON, 17 A. 3 R,,
(N. L.), Henrico Co., in Varina Par;
N. side of James Riv; on head of the
Long Field patent; adj. Thomas Taylor;
& William Burton; 15 July 1717, p.
324. Imp. of: Alexander Hatton.

PHILIP PARKER & ‘CHARLES
PARKER, 50 acs. (Escheat L.), Accomack Co; near head of Nandewe Cr;
adj. land formerly of Anthony Johnson;
Thomas Middleton; & Robert Andrews;
15 July 1717, p. 332. Escheated from
Anthony Johnson, dec’d., by inquisition.
under John Custis, Esqr., Esch’r., &c.
2 Lbs. Tobacco, &c.

RICHARD TALLY, 181 acs. (N.
L.), Pr. Geo. Co; on S, side of Appamattox Riv; below Wontopock Ford;
15 July 1717, p. 337. 20 Shill.

GILBERT IVY, 250 acs. (N. L.),
Surry Co; on S, side of Mahezin Riv;
by Keaway Swamp; adj. Mathew Smart;
22 Jan. 1717, p, 349. 25 Shill.

THOMAS STANTON, of Staff. Co;
214 acs. (N. L.), Essex Co., in St.
Mary’s Par; iu the fork of Rappa. River;
22 Jan. 1717, p. 354. 25 Shill.

THOMAS BOYD, JUNR., 292 acs.
(N. L.), Up. Par. of Nansemond Co;
24 Jan. 1717, p. 359. 30 Shill.

JOHN BARNES, JUNR., & WILLIAM BARNES, 365 acs. (N. L.),
Henrico Co; on N. side of James Riv;
in a fork of the N. br. of Tuckahoe;
on Wadkins Br; 12 July 1718, p. 379.
40 Shill.

JAMES JOHNSON, 400 acs, (N.
L.), Henrico Co; on N. side of James
Riv; adj. Cha. Eavens; John Johnson;
Joseph Woodson; & Benja. Woodson;
12 July 1718, p. 380. 40 Shill.

THOMAS AVENT, 190 acs. (N. L.);
Surry Co; on NE side of the Three
Creeks; 14 July 1718, p. 405. 20 Shill.

LAMBERT ZELL, 215 acs. (N. L.),
Surry Co; on S, side of Nottoway River;
14 July 1718, p. 406. 25 Shill.

GEORGE FREEMAN, 400 acs. (N.
L.), Henrico Co; on E, side of Tuckahoe main branch; & down Deep run;
22 Jan. 1718, p. 408. 40 Shill.

EDWARD MOORE, 400 acs. (N.
L.), New Kent Co., in St. Paul’s Parish;
22 Jan, 1718, p. 413. 40 Shill.

JOHN BALLIE, 69 acs. (N. L.),
Eliza, City Co; adj, George Walker;
Thomas Reade; Eatton’s School land}
ail
& Matthew Watts’ line; 22 Jan. 1718,
p. 416. 10 Shill.

JEAN JOUANY, 650 acs. (N. L.);
Henrico Co; on S. side of James Riv;
beg, on the main upper br. of the
Monakin Cr; on John Pleasants’ line;
to upper broad rock of Fine Cr; to
mouth of a meadow br. parting this
& land of Capt. Jefferson; 11 July 1719,
p. 421. 3 Lbs., Money, & Imp. of: John
Jones,

JOHN SNEAD, 195 acs. (N. L.),
New Kent Co; adj. lands of Giles;
Harrilson;* Meeks; Hooper; & Tinsley;
V1 July 1719, p. 439. 20 Shill. *(Note:
In the absence of punctuation, this may
refer to one person, i. e. Giles Harrilson.)

JOHN WALL, 200 acs. (N. L.),
Surry Co; on S, side of Maherrin River;
11 July 1719, p. 447. 20 Shill.

RALPH JACKSON, 25 acs. (N. L.),
Surry Co; on N, side of Maherin River;
adj. Robert Hix; & Henry Wych’s line;
11 July 1719, p. 447. 5 Shill.

ROBERT SLAUGHTER, 470 acs.
(N. L.), Essex Co., in St. Mary’s Par;
on §. side of the Rapidanna River; a
little above the mouth of Hunting Run;
20 Feb. 1719, p. 456. 50 Shill.
